Tuberculosis is one of the leading causes of death worldwide. Twenty-two high burden
countries contributed to the majority of worldwide tuberculosis cases in 2015. Health care
workers are at high risk of acquiring tuberculosis through occupational exposure.

Databases including MEDLINE (Ovid), EMBASE (Ovid), CINAHL (Ovid) and ISI Web of

ords on relevant medical subject headings (MeSH) terms of LTBI and health care providers.
Literature was systematically reviewed using EPPI-Reviewer4 software. Prevalence and
